## Writing Style

- Use **tables** for comparisons and lists of options
- Use **numbered lists** for sequential steps or ranked items
- Use **bullet points** for unordered lists
- Include **status badges** (🔴 Stub, 🟡 WIP, ✅ Complete) in tables
- Use **blockquotes** for important notes and warnings
- Use **code blocks** with appropriate language hints

---

## Checklist for New Patterns

When adding a new composite pattern:

- [ ] Create detailed pattern document following the structure above
- [ ] Include both AI and non-AI automation examples
- [ ] Add diagrams (conceptual, flow, reuse)
- [ ] Update README.md with synopsis and link
- [ ] Update Pattern Index table in README.md
- [ ] Add/update operator documentation in `04-subsystems/operators/`
- [ ] Update CRD reference in `04-subsystems/operators/crd-reference.md`
- [ ] Cross-reference from related subsystem docs
- [ ] Update this planned patterns list
